<ITEM><HI>Prop. III.</HI> The Immortal Souls of Just men when in a state of Sepa<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">ation from their Bodies, are made Perfect. <HI>p. 64</HI></ITEM>
<ITEM>For, <HI>1.</HI> They are perfectly delivered from all afflictive Evils. <HI>p. 65</HI> to <HI>71</HI></ITEM>
<ITEM><HI>2</HI> From Sin. <HI>ibid</HI> to <HI>76</HI></ITEM>
<ITEM><HI>3.</HI> Th<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters"> attain unto a great Perfection in Knowledge. <HI>ibid</HI></ITEM>
<ITEM><HI>4.</HI> To a blessed Perfection in Grace and Holiness. <HI>p. 81</HI></ITEM>
<ITEM><HI>Pr<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">p IV</HI> The Spirits of Just men are made Perfect at the <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters">sta<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">t when their Bodies Dy. <HI>p. 84</HI></ITEM>
